@startuml Mediator Pattern
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

title Mediator Pattern - Component Communication

actor "External\nTrigger" as Trigger

package "Mediator" {
    component [Mediator\nCore] as Mediator
    component [Component\nContainer] as Container
    
    package "Flow Actions" {
        component [Action 1] as Action1
        component [Action 2] as Action2
        component [Action 3] as Action3
    }
}

package "Components" {
    component [Risk\nCalculator] as Risk
    component [Portfolio\nAggregator] as Portfolio
    component [Strategy\nRegistry] as Registry
}

' Ownership relationships
Container -down-> Risk : owns\n(unique_ptr)
Container -down-> Portfolio : owns\n(unique_ptr)
Container -down-> Registry : owns\n(unique_ptr)

' Action creation
Mediator -down-> Action1 : creates
Mediator -down-> Action2 : creates
Mediator -down-> Action3 : creates

' Actions borrow components
Action1 .right.> Risk : borrows\n(reference)
Action1 .right.> Portfolio : borrows\n(reference)

Action2 .right.> Portfolio : borrows\n(reference)
Action2 .right.> Registry : borrows\n(reference)

Action3 .right.> Risk : borrows\n(reference)
Action3 .right.> Registry : borrows\n(reference)

' Flow execution
Trigger -right-> Mediator : executeFlow()
Mediator -down-> Action1 : execute()
Action1 -down-> Action2 : next
Action2 -down-> Action3 : next

note right of Mediator
  **Responsibilities:**
  - Owns all components
  - Creates flow actions
  - Manages thread safety
  - Executes flows sequentially
end note

note bottom of Action1
  **Actions only route data:**
  1. Get component reference
  2. Call component method
  3. Return result
  
  NO business logic!
end note

note bottom of Risk
  **Components are:**
  - Single-threaded
  - Stateless (or manage own state)
  - Testable in isolation
  - No mutexes needed
end note

@enduml
